==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[habēn]]'', {{OS.}} ''[[hebbian]]'', from Germanic ''*hab-æ-'' "have", related to {{L.}} ''[[capere]]'' "to [[grip]]", and {{L.}} ''[[habere]]'' "to have".

===Verb===
'''haben'''

# to [[have]], to [[possess]]
# auxiliary verb used to form the [[perfect tense]]

====Conjugations====
present
* ich '''[[habe]]''' ''I have''
* du '''[[hast]]''' ''you have''
* er, sie, es '''[[hat]]''' '' he, she, it has''
* wir, sie '''[[haben]]''' ''we, they have''
* ihr '''[[habt]]''' ''you have''

perfect
* '''[[gehabt]]'''

